      • getAlternativeforcutoff

        public TField getAlternativeforcutoff()
        Returns the Alternativeforcutoff

        Field description: Alternative for cut-off exceeded. If the R & S option could not be chosen because the cutoff was exceeded then the alternative for cut-off exceeded is checked to determine the processing required. R & S provides the following alternatives for them 1. NEXT (N) The next available R & S option under the same Contract Category is checked. 2. ADVANCE (A) The due date is advanced. (Refer to the date processing on how this is carried out) 3. REPAIR (R) The payment is routed to Repair for a manual review. 4. Country (C) Switch to Country level Contract. Applicable only on a PTY contract. The Contract table is checked to determine the applicable CTY contract. R & S based is carried out based on that contract

        Validation Rules: 1) Mandatory. 2) Dropdown with allowed values A,C,N & R. 3) Option C is only allowed for ContractType 'PTY'.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The Alternativeforcutoff

        Field description: Defines the rate at which the Treasury unit will buy or sell foreign Currency from/to the marketing units. The Final exchange rate quoted to Customers (Customer Rate) will be determined by the addition or subtraction of the appropriate Customer Spread to/from the Treasury Buy/Sell Rate. This value can only be imposed if the Exchange/Customer Rate is not imposed. If not imposed the value that is entered will be ignored and taken from T24 Currency table.

        public TField getCreditvaluedateimposedflag()
        Returns the Creditvaluedateimposedflag

        Field description: This field specifies whether the credit value date is imposed or can still be overwritten by the date component. In case the impose flag is lacking but the credit value date is specified, the manual input is more a suggestion towards the system. In case the impose flag is present and the credit value date is specified, the manual input is a hard requirement to be taken into account by the date component, even though the given date is a non-working day.

      • getCutoffshiftdays

        public TField getCutoffshiftdays()
        Returns the Cutoffshiftdays

        Field description: Cut-off Shift This is the number of business days to include in the date formulas when payment is after cut-off but we still want to process it today (ASAP). Adding this shift means that Credit Value Date is accordingly shifted in future. If we are working in ALAP then we dont apply cut-off shift but rather warehouse the payment till next working day.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The Cutoffshiftdays

      • getCutofftime

        public TField getCutofftime()
        Returns the Cutofftime

        Field description: Specifies the time after which the channel cannot be used for routing payments on a given day. The value will be used in Routing & Settlement processing and Dates processing to determine if a payment has passed cut-off time for a particular channel or not. Routing & Settlement can decide to find alternative channel to settle the payment or bump the due date by 1 day so that it can be processed on next day. Action to be taken will be setup driven and defined in Routing & Settlement. In case of incoming payments, CVD (Credit Value Date) is increased by cut-off shift and the payment is processed on the same day. Validation Rules: 5 characters of type TIME. Value will be in HH:MM format.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The Cutofftime

        public void setAlternativeforcutoff(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for Alternativeforcutoff
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Alternative for cut-off exceeded. If the R & S option could not be chosen because the cutoff was exceeded then the alternative for cut-off exceeded is checked to determine the processing required. R & S provides the following alternatives for them 1. NEXT (N) The next available R & S option under the same Contract Category is checked. 2. ADVANCE (A) The due date is advanced. (Refer to the date processing on how this is carried out) 3. REPAIR (R) The payment is routed to Repair for a manual review. 4. Country (C) Switch to Country level Contract. Applicable only on a PTY contract. The Contract table is checked to determine the applicable CTY contract. R & S based is carried out based on that contract

        Validation Rules: 1) Mandatory. 2) Dropdown with allowed values A,C,N & R. 3) Option C is only allowed for ContractType 'PTY'.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field specifies whether the credit value date is imposed or can still be overwritten by the date component. In case the impose flag is present and the credit value date is specified, the manual input is a hard requirement to be taken into account by the date component, even though the given date is a non-working day.

      • setCutoffshiftdays

        public void setCutoffshiftdays(TField value)
        Set the specified value for Cutoffshiftdays
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Cut-off Shift This is the number of business days to include in the date formulas when payment is after cut-off but we still want to process it today (ASAP). Adding this shift means that Credit Value Date is accordingly shifted in future. If we are working in ALAP then we dont apply cut-off shift but rather warehouse the payment till next working day.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setCutofftime

        public void setCutofftime(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for Cutofftime
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Specifies the time after which the channel cannot be used for routing payments on a given day. The value will be used in Routing & Settlement processing and Dates processing to determine if a payment has passed cut-off time for a particular channel or not. Routing & Settlement can decide to find alternative channel to settle the payment or bump the due date by 1 day so that it can be processed on next day. Action to be taken will be setup driven and defined in Routing & Settlement. In case of incoming payments, CVD (Credit Value Date) is increased by cut-off shift and the payment is processed on the same day. Validation Rules: 5 characters of type TIME. Value will be in HH:MM format.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        Set the specified value for Debitvaluedateimposedflag
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field specifies whether the debit value date is imposed or can still be overwritten by the date component. In case the impose flag is lacking but the debit value date is specified, the manual input is more a suggestion towards the system. In case the impose flag is present and the debit value date is specified, the manual input is a hard requirement to be taken into account by the date component, even though the given date is a non-working day. Possible values: "Y" " "
